    "rationale": "Twelve of thirteen V&V 40 credibility factors meet or exceed required levels. The single shortfall (Test conditions, achieved 2 vs. required 3) is accepted because ASTM F1717 specifies a single standardized configuration representing the conservative worst-case loading scenario for posterior spinal fixation systems. All quantitative acceptance criteria (E/uval <1.96, percentage difference <10%) are satisfied for all three QoIs. The overall credibility evidence is judged sufficient to support the regulatory submission decision. Note: this package conforms to ProfileMinimal; the digital signature workflow is pending and no signature field is present.",
